Related C++ code:
  - emBorder.h:321-341 (struct TkResources): holds the same image fields as ToolkitImages,
    plus 3 additional fields not in Rust: ImgDir, ImgDirUp, ImgTunnel.
  - emBorder.cpp:47-61: loads TGA files via emGetResImage() from res/emCore/toolkit/ at runtime.
    C++ loads from filesystem at runtime; Rust embeds via include_bytes!() at compile time.
  - C++ resource directory: res/emCore/toolkit/ with finalize script at
    res/emCore/toolkit/src/toolkit-finalize.pl
  - Rust resource directory: res/toolkit/ (15 TGA files; C++ has 18 — adds Dir.tga, DirUp.tga, Tunnel.tga)
    Note: Tunnel.tga exists in Rust res/toolkit/ but is not loaded by ToolkitImages.

Structural differences:
  - In C++, TkResources is a nested struct inside emBorder, loaded via emGetResImage() at runtime.
    In Rust, ToolkitImages is a standalone module with compile-time embedding (include_bytes!).
  - C++ uses a shared resource context (emRootContext) for deduplication; Rust uses thread_local OnceCell.
  - Rust is missing 3 of 18 C++ images: ImgDir, ImgDirUp, ImgTunnel.
    (Tunnel.tga is present in res/toolkit/ but not loaded.)

OPEN QUESTIONS:
  - Why is Tunnel.tga present in res/toolkit/ but not loaded by ToolkitImages?
  - Will ImgDir and ImgDirUp be needed when emFileSelectionBox or emFileDialog is ported?
